DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260810
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260811
SUMMARY:Deadline: Day Job: Short Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:Short film competition from Day Job Films created to give auteu
 r directors full creative freedom\, awarding a production budget of up to 
 GBP 7\,000 to make a short film with no producer interference or commercia
 l agenda. Open to animation\, live-action and documentary projects. Runs i
 n three rounds: (1) a pitch deck outlining concept\, story\, key character
 s and visual style\; (2) a full script for those who progress\; and (3) an
  interview to discuss the vision and execution. A panel of industry profes
 sionals judges the pitch deck\, script and interview\, with at least one t
 eam member reading each pitch deck and script in full. The winner receives
  full creative control over the project. ELIGIBILITY: applicants can be fr
 om anywhere worldwide\, but all production must take place in the UK\; app
 licants must have a producer on board who is separate from the director/wr
 iter. Applicants may optionally include a plan for adapting the script int
 o a feature-length film (this does not affect the outcome). Submissions op
 en February 10\, 2026 and close August 10\, 2026. Enquiries: hello@dayjobf
 ilms.com.\n\nOrganisation: Day Job Films\nLocation: Worldwide applicants\;
  all production must take place in the UK\nAward: Production budget of up 
 to GBP 7\,000\, with full creative control and no producer or external int
 erference. No application fee.\nDuration: Per short film project\n\nMore: 
 https://www.dayjobfilms.com/short-film-fund
URL:https://www.dayjobfilms.com/short-film-fund
LOCATION:Worldwide applicants\; all production must take place in the UK
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blackstone-publishing-novel-initiative-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260609
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260610
SUMMARY:Deadline: The Blackstone Publishing Novel Initiative 2026 (with The
  Black List)
DESCRIPTION:A partnership between The Black List and Blackstone Publishing 
 to identify an unpublished manuscript for a $25\,000 publishing deal. The 
 Black List helps Blackstone shortlist outstanding manuscripts submitted on
  blcklst.com during the submission period. Open to manuscripts in all genr
 es\, with particular interest in work that elevates familiar themes (love\
 , adventure\, guilt\, desire\, betrayal\, family\, identity\, obsession) f
 rom fresh\, compelling perspectives\, especially thrillers\, high-concept 
 mysteries\, romances and horror. REQUIREMENTS: post an original manuscript
  on blcklst.com\, receive at least one evaluation while hosted there (once
  evaluated\, a manuscript can be submitted to any eligible partnership at 
 no additional cost)\, and opt in to the program during the submission peri
 od. Submitted manuscripts must not be under contract elsewhere\; no featur
 e\, pilot\, play or musical submissions are eligible. Applicants must be a
 t least 18 and the sole owner of all rights to wholly original material\, 
 and must agree to the Submission Agreement (which includes legally binding
  terms such as arbitration). If selected\, the writer may enter into a boo
 k deal negotiated in good faith. Writing teams are allowed\, but every mem
 ber must comply and all must opt out if any member becomes ineligible. Not
 e: submitting requires being logged in to blcklst.com with an uploaded pro
 ject (the site charges separately for hosting and evaluations). Deadline J
 une 9\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation: The Black List and Blackstone Publishing\nL
 ocation: Online (manuscripts hosted on blcklst.com)\nAward: A $25\,000 pub
 lishing deal with Blackstone Publishing for the selected manuscript.\nDura
 tion: Submission period November 20\, 2025 to June 9\, 2026\n\nMore: https
 ://blcklst.com/programs/blackstone-publishing-novel-initiative
URL:https://blcklst.com/programs/blackstone-publishing-novel-initiative
LOCATION:Online (manuscripts hosted on blcklst.com)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kamp-creative-body-institute-lesbos-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260524
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260525
SUMMARY:Deadline: KAMP: Creative Body Institute Residency\, Lesbos\, Greece
  2026
DESCRIPTION:KAMP is a communal residency from the artist-run non-profit Cre
 ative Body Institute\, inviting queer-identifying artists to an ecological
  hermitage on Lesbos Island\, Greece\, to develop work exploring queer eco
 logies\, queer temporality\, and ecofeminist practices through a human and
  more-than-human\, life-art ethos. CBI seeks artists whose practices engag
 e embodiment\, interdependence and temporality through performance\, insta
 llation\, sound\, dance or experimental visual work. FOUR TRACKS: (1) Expe
 rimental Media and Performativity\, Jul 22-Aug 10\; (2) Relational and Sit
 e-Responsive Work\, Aug 14-Sep 2\; (3) Body-Based and Durational Practice\
 , Sep 6-24/26\; (4) Writer in Residence (dates coinciding with one of the 
 above\, for those focused on exegesis\, a publication\, or writing about p
 rior embodied/artistic research). 5-7 artists are selected per cohort. Hou
 sing is simple cabin-based accommodation for relational living (Queer Fami
 ly Cabin for 2-3\, Cozy Cabin for solitude\, Sanctuary Cabin for 2 sharing
 )\, with communal outdoor kitchen\, shower house and bathrooms\; this is a
 n off-grid\, sustainable environment (solar power\, conscious water use\, 
 limited wifi). Artists must be comfortable with close communal living\, sh
 ared rhythms\, a collective food system (primarily vegetarian and pescatar
 ian\, sourced from local farmers)\, and unpaved terrain (which may be diff
 icult for those with mobility impairments). INCLUDED: accommodation\, shar
 ed indoor/outdoor workspaces\, groceries for shared meals and staff suppor
 t\, two on-site CBI artist-faculty\, mentorship and feedback\, structured 
 and informal group programming\, work-in-progress sharing\, and photo/vide
 o documentation. APPLICATION: online form (no draft saving) with project d
 escription (350 words) tied to the chosen track\, 1-2 work samples\, optio
 nal portfolio\, artist bio(s) (350 words)\, and three short-answer questio
 ns\; you may respond in any language. Apply individually (willing to share
 )\, as a duo\, or as a trio/small group. Deadline May 24\, 2026 (23:59 CET
 )\; virtual interviews May 25-29\; final notifications June 1. Confirm wit
 hin 5 days of acceptance with the EUR 100 deposit.\n\nOrganisation: Creati
 ve Body Institute (CBI)\nLocation: Lesbos Island\, Greece (eco-art hermita
 ge in an olive grove on Mount Lepetymnos)\nAward: Co-funded residency. Tot
 al cost per artist EUR 2\,500\; CBI funds EUR 1\,350\, so the artist contr
 ibution is EUR 1\,150 (plus a EUR 100 non-refundable deposit deducted from
  that contribution). Does not include travel\, visas\, airport transfers\,
  insurance or personal food. One full contribution waiver is available per
  cohort (request on the form\; reviewed after selection\, based on financi
 al need and cohort balance).\nDuration: Roughly 3-week residency per track
 \; tracks run July 22 to September 26\, 2026\n\nMore: https://www.creative
 body.org/kamp
URL:https://www.creativebody.org/kamp
LOCATION:Lesbos Island\, Greece (eco-art hermitage in an olive grove on Mou
 nt Lepetymnos)
END:VEVENT
