UID:bam-scanteia-bucharest-residency-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Deadline: Bayt AlMamzar x Scanteia: Bucharest Residency Exchange 20
 26-2027
DESCRIPTION:An international exchange between Bayt AlMamzar (BAM)\, an arti
 st-run space in Dubai\, and Scanteia\, an artist-run space in Bucharest\, 
 inviting UAE-based artists to undertake individual month-long residencies 
 in Bucharest across 2026-2027\, followed by a joint exhibition curated by 
 Scanteia. Two artists are selected for non-overlapping residencies (Aug-Se
 p 2026 and mid-March to mid-April 2027). Scanteia provides a private ~50 s
 qm studio with live-in accommodation\, a flight subsidy up to $500\, a $50
 0 artist fee\, a local transport card\, weekly studio visits with Romanian
  curators and gallerists\, study trips (MARe\, MNAC\, EVA Foundation)\, ac
 cess to specialised equipment (large-scale inkjet printing\, photography s
 tudio\, wood workshop\, scanners)\, exhibition space\, and documentation/p
 ublication support via BAM's publishing arm BAMBAM. ELIGIBILITY: open to v
 isual artists\, researchers and practitioners currently based in the UAE\,
  aged 18+\, at any career stage\; a valid UAE residence visa is required a
 t the time of application. No nationality restriction\, but applicants wit
 hout an EU or Emirati passport will need a Schengen visa (Scanteia provide
 s an invitation letter). They seek artists with a developed practice and a
  specific\, articulable reason to spend time in Bucharest (exploration\, r
 esearch\, production or exchange)\, with no fixed theme or medium. Deadlin
 e 7 June 2026. Contact hello@baytalmazmar.org.\n\nOrganisation: Bayt AlMam
 zar (BAM) and Scanteia\nLocation: Residency in Bucharest\, Romania (applic
 ants must be UAE-based)\nAward: Funded residency: private ~50 sqm studio w
 ith accommodation at Atelierele Scanteia\, flight covered up to $500\, $50
 0 artist fee\, local transport card\, access to large-format inkjet printi
 ng\, photo studio\, wood workshop and scanners\, plus a curated joint exhi
 bition. No application fee.\nDuration: One month (Residency 1: Aug-Sep 202
 6\; Residency 2: mid-March to mid-April 2027)\, with a joint exhibition en
 d of April 2027\n\nMore: https://www.prazzlearts.com/opportunities/open-ca
 ll-for-artist-residency-bam--scnteia-bucharest-2027
URL:https://www.prazzlearts.com/opportunities/open-call-for-artist-residenc
 y-bam--scnteia-bucharest-2027
LOCATION:Residency in Bucharest\, Romania (applicants must be UAE-based)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fpp-residency-exhibition-konstkollektivet-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
SUMMARY:Deadline: FPP Residency & Exhibition 2026 (Konstkollektivet / Flowe
 r Power Photography)
DESCRIPTION:Residency and exhibition for visual artists whose practice enga
 ges with experimental\, alternative and/or critical image-making (analogue
  processes\, archives or hybrid approaches)\, with a particular interest i
 n image-making as a way of living and thinking alongside the planet and ot
 her beings\, embracing slowness\, collaboration and more-than-human care. 
 Organised by Konstkollektivet with Flower Power Photography (an artistic r
 esearch project by Sam McCarthy and Lasse Lindqvist on non-violence\, ecol
 ogy and more-than-human ethics)\, Centrum for fotografi\, and Artist in Co
 existence (AiC). Includes a 14-day residency on the island of Orust (3-15 
 August)\, a process presentation\, a workshop contribution at Konstkollekt
 ivet (15-16 August)\, and participation in a group exhibition at Konstpark
 en opening 1 September\, plus accommodation\, an artist fee (7\,000 SEK)\,
  exhibition fee (3\,400 SEK)\, and travel support up to 4\,000 SEK. ELIGIB
 ILITY: European-based visual artists of all ages and nationalities. APPLIC
 ATION: one PDF (max 10MB) with a project proposal/motivation (max 1 page)\
 , artist statement (max 150 words)\, CV (1 page) and portfolio (max 5 page
 s) to residens@konstkollektivet.se\, subject line 'Name_LastName_FPP_Resid
 ency'\, by 14 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Konstkollektivet\, with Flower P
 ower Photography\, Centrum for fotografi and Artist in Coexistence (AiC)\n
 Location: Orust and Molndal\, Sweden\nAward: Artist fee 7\,000 SEK plus ex
 hibition fee 3\,400 SEK\, travel support up to 4\,000 SEK (slow travel by 
 train/bus encouraged)\, and accommodation for the whole period. Plus facil
 itation\, mentorship and research support. No application fee. (Amounts in
  SEK\, incl. VAT where applicable.)\nDuration: 14-day residency 3-17 Augus
 t 2026\; group exhibition opens 1 September 2026\n\nMore: https://www.kons
 tkollektivet.se/open-call-fpp-residency-exhibition/
URL:https://www.konstkollektivet.se/open-call-fpp-residency-exhibition/
LOCATION:Orust and Molndal\, Sweden
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:biennale-college-cinema-immersive-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260617T130707Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260706
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260707
SUMMARY:Deadline: Biennale College Cinema - Immersive 2026 (11th edition)
DESCRIPTION:La Biennale di Venezia's Biennale College Cinema - Immersive se
 lects 12 immersive international concepts (of which 2 Italian)\, up to 30 
 minutes long\, that can be made within a EUR 75\,000 budget and completed 
 for exhibition at the 2027 Venice International Film Festival. Projects mu
 st be realisable only using immersive technologies. The call is open 12 Ma
 y to 6 July 2026 (23:59 CEST) to teams of a director and a producer from a
 nywhere in the world\, at their first\, second or third immersive project.
  Selected teams sign an agreement with La Biennale and take part in the fu
 ll project-led programme. ELIGIBILITY: applications welcomed from people i
 n film\, gaming\, theatre\, dance\, opera\, visual arts and other creative
  fields\; applicants apply in director-and-producer teams. Film-world appl
 icants need experience in short films\, documentaries and/or features\; th
 ose from outside film need a body of work demonstrating understanding of n
 arrative and spatial concerns. No age limit and no participation fee\; par
 ticipants cover their own travel. Those already invited to a previous BCC 
 Immersive workshop cannot reapply. APPLICATION (in English): project conce
 pt\, full treatment with director and producer statements\, a director's v
 ision (mood board/project-book/video)\, up to two previous works\, a total
  budget up to EUR 75\,000\, biographies/filmographies\, production company
  profile\, a 3-minute joint video presentation\, an audience engagement pl
 an\, rights disclosure\, and a signed director-producer agreement. Contact
 : college-cinema@labiennale.org.\n\nOrganisation: La Biennale di Venezia\n
 Location: Venice\, Italy (workshops in person\; exhibition at the 2027 Ven
 ice International Film Festival)\nAward: Up to EUR 75\,000 to produce a ne
 w immersive project (up to 30 minutes)\, completed for exhibition at the 2
 027 Venice International Film Festival. No participation fee. NOTE: partic
 ipants must cover their own travel to the workshops and events.\nDuration:
  Year-long project-led programme leading to a 2027 Venice Film Festival ex
 hibition\n\nMore: https://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2026/bcc-11-immersi
 ve-call
URL:https://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2026/bcc-11-immersive-call
LOCATION:Venice\, Italy (workshops in person\; exhibition at the 2027 Venic
 e International Film Festival)
END:VEVENT
