 rging/rolling/metal powders\, awarded within the Arte Laguna Prize 2026. T
 HEME: 'the journey of steel in its crossing from hot to cold' - a metamorp
 hosis of matter from incandescent casting to a cooled\, smooth\, precise s
 urface\; works should evoke this transition. FORMAT: hangable panel or can
 vas\, dimensions between 1.5x1.5 m (minimum) and 3x2 m (maximum)\; unconve
 ntional materials encouraged. THREE AWARDS to nominated works: EUR 7\,000 
 first\, EUR 4\,000 second\, EUR 3\,000 third (taxes included)\, paid after
  the work is presented. IMPORTANT CONDITION: the winning works become the 
 property of FOMAS Group\, with the artists ceding ownership and rights of 
 economic use\, reproduction\, communication to the public\, exhibition\, d
 istribution and digitisation for institutional and promotional purposes. A
 PPLY by submitting via the Arte Laguna Prize portal (which has a registrat
 ion fee\, approx. EUR 97-122 for the full prize). Registration for the FOM
 AS Special Award closes 1 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: FOMAS Group (in coll
 aboration with Arte Laguna Prize)\nLocation: Italy (FOMAS HQ Lecco\; prese
 nted within Arte Laguna at Arsenale Nord\, Venice)\nAward: First prize EUR
  7\,000\; second EUR 4\,000\; third EUR 3\,000 (all taxes included). NOTE:
  works are entered via the Arte Laguna Prize\, which has a registration fe
 e (approx. EUR 97-122). The winning works become FOMAS Group property (rig
 hts of economic use\, reproduction\, communication to the public\, exhibit
 ion\, distribution and digitisation transferred to FOMAS).\nDuration: One-
 off special prize awarded within Arte Laguna Prize 2026\n\nMore: https://a
 rtelagunaprize.com/network/fomas-group-italy/
URL:https://artelagunaprize.com/network/fomas-group-italy/
