 l theme (max 2 pages)\, optional contribution proposal to daily life at So
 nnenberg\, work samples\, and proof of illness/accident insurance. TIMELIN
 E: Deadline 7 June 2026\; residency mid-January to mid-April 2027. NOTE: R
 esidents contribute through events (workshops\, exhibitions\, concerts) an
 d conclude with a final public exhibition or presentation.\n\nOrganisation
 : Stiftung Villa Sonnenberg\nLocation: Lenzburg\, Aargau\, Switzerland\nAw
 ard: CHF 600/month per-diem (CHF 20/day) + free accommodation in private m
 odern studio with kitchen and bathroom + use of workshop and music rehears
 al room. No application or entry fee.\nDuration: 3 months (mid-January to 
 mid-April 2027)\; minimum 80% attendance\n\nMore: https://www.villasonnenb
 erg.ch/en/
