DESCRIPTION:Stiftung Villa Sonnenberg's 2027 Artist-in-Residence programme 
 on the annual theme 'Myths'. ELIGIBILITY: Professional artists working in 
 visual arts and music. THEME: Artistic works engaging with myths in their 
 social\, personal\, or political dimensions\; future-oriented approaches w
 elcome (e.g.\, myths in digital public spheres\, gaming cultures\, AI-gene
 rated visual worlds\, or projects considering Villa Sonnenberg in Lenzburg
  and the Aargau canton). DISCIPLINES: Visual arts\, music. FUNDING: Free s
 ingle-use accommodation in a modern top-floor studio with private kitchen 
 and bathroom\; daily allowance of CHF 20 (CHF 600/month). Access to studio
  house with a 20 sqm workshop\, 20 sqm music rehearsal room\, and garden. 
 APPLY: Read the 'Open Call Artist in Residence 2027' document on villasonn
 enberg.ch and submit CV with photo\, project outline referencing the annua
 l theme (max 2 pages)\, optional contribution proposal to daily life at So
 nnenberg\, work samples\, and proof of illness/accident insurance. TIMELIN
 E: Deadline 7 June 2026\; residency mid-May to mid-August 2027. NOTE: Resi
 dents contribute through events (workshops\, exhibitions\, concerts) and c
 onclude with a final public exhibition or presentation.\n\nOrganisation: S
 tiftung Villa Sonnenberg\nLocation: Lenzburg\, Aargau\, Switzerland\nAward
 : CHF 600/month per-diem (CHF 20/day) + free accommodation in private mode
 rn studio with kitchen and bathroom + use of workshop and music rehearsal 
 room. No application or entry fee.\nDuration: 3 months (mid-May to mid-Aug
 ust 2027)\; minimum 80% attendance\n\nMore: https://www.villasonnenberg.ch
 /en/
URL:https://www.villasonnenberg.ch/en/
LOCATION:Lenzburg\, Aargau\, Switzerland
