SUMMARY:Deadline: Kometa Fellows 2026: Field Journalism\, Photography\, and
  Writing
DESCRIPTION:Kometa\, a French literary and journalism magazine\, awards fel
 lowships to journalists\, writers\, and photographers documenting reality 
 in contexts of war\, censorship\, or severe social and political tensions.
  Projects must be rooted in direct field experience and focused on contemp
 orary rather than historical events. Projects already under a contractual 
 agreement are ineligible. AMOUNT: €10\,000 per Fellow. WHAT FELLOWS RECE
 IVE: one year of funding\; publication of the completed project (partial o
 r full) in Kometa\; opportunity to contribute to the monthly newsletter\; 
 mentorship through editorial collaboration. 2026 FOCUS AREAS: disinformati
 on and narrative wars\; political and social changes in the Gulf. DEADLINE
 : 31 July 2026. APPLY via the Tally form linked from the Kometa website. C
 ontact: fellows@kometarevue.com.\n\nOrganisation: Kometa (French literary 
 and journalism magazine)\nLocation: Remote / field-based (international)\n
 Award: €10\,000 per Fellow. No application fee.\nDuration: One year of f
 unding for field work and research\n\nMore: https://kometarevue.com/page/f
 ellows
URL:https://kometarevue.com/page/fellows
LOCATION:Remote / field-based (international)
